57.7	Columbo	Columbo	Columbo is an American mystery crime fiction television film series, starring Peter Falk as Lieutenant Columbo, a homicide detective with the Los Angeles Police Department. The character and television show were created by William Link and Richard Levinson. The show popularized the inverted detective story format. With the exception of a few episodes, almost every episode began by showing the commission of the crime and its perpetrator. The series has no "whodunit" element. The plot mainly revolves around how the perpetrator, whose identity is already known to the audience, will finally be caught and exposed by Columbo.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/ad/ColumboDVD3.jpg/250px-ColumboDVD3.jpg
